Class PCodeVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
      • be.unamur.info.b314.compiler.B314BaseVisitor<java.lang.Object>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    be.unamur.info.b314.compiler.B314Visitor<java.lang.Object>, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeVisitor<java.lang.Object>

    public class PCodeVisitor
extends be.unamur.info.b314.compiler.B314BaseVisitor<java.lang.Object>
    The PCodeVisitor method generates PCode for various contexts, depending on which context is being visited by the visitor. The first context to be visited by the program is the ProgramContext.
    Author:
    Valentin Eggermont - valentin.eggermont@student.unamur.be, William Turatsinze - william.turatsinze@student.unamur.be, Thomas Vanhaeren - thomas.vanhaeren@student.unamur.be
